  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 19 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1250 mg
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-brussels-sprout-bacon-flatbreads-64f8885828f67f0f15b17e06
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring @cream cheese{½%cup} to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Lay flat and thinly slice crosswise into shreds. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.

Heat a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Return pan used for bacon to medium-high heat; add Brussels sprouts in a single layer. Cook, undisturbed, until edges are dark brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until Brussels sprouts begin to wilt, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} (arrange in a single layer to help them cool faster!). Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add half the @dried rosemary{1%tsp} (all for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{10%seconds}. Add onion and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp}, ⅓ cup water, and @sugar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4); cook, stirring, until onion is caramelized and jammy, ~{3-4%minutes}, adding splashes of water if necessary to prevent burning.

Stir in wilted Brussels sprouts; taste and season with salt and pepper.

Place @flatbreads{2}(dimpled sides down) on a #baking sheet{}; toast on top rack until flatbreads are golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between two sheets; toast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through toasting.)

> Line the baking sheet with foil first for easy cleanup!

Once flatbreads are toasted, flip over (dimpled sides up) and evenly spread with cream cheese. Top with Brussels sprout mixture and chopped bacon.

Return flatbreads to oven; bake until flatbread edges are golden brown, ~{5-6%minutes}. (Watch carefully so flatbreads don't burn!)

Slice flatbreads into quarters. Divide between plates and serve.